   "source": [
    "# Basic statistics and visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "9a094304-ba0d-4025-b2e4-4c6cb23eb0a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import admix\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import dapgen\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "7293cf46-c058-452b-83b8-a6e94c1bd396",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "2024-02-07 16:27:53 [info     ] Example data set already exists at .//example_data, skip downloading\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# read the simulated dataset\n",
    "admix.dataset.download_simulated_example_data()\n",
    "dset = admix.io.read_dataset(\"example_data/CEU-YRI\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3bedb93b-b59e-4456-b1e2-0776a95e9ea2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Local ancestry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "70bbfdaa-1328-4826-b370-951ca2547711",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x450 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot local ancestries for the first 10 individuals\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(4, 3), dpi=150)\n",
    "admix.plot.lanc(dset=dset, max_indiv=10)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "006b060b-bb94-4052-851d-3be6ff0b77c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x225 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot the average local ancestry per-person\n",
    "lanc = dset.lanc.compute()\n",
    "avg_lanc = lanc.mean(axis=(0, 2))\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(4, 1.5), dpi=150)\n",
    "ax.hist(avg_lanc, bins=20, edgecolor=\"black\", linewidth=0.5, density=True)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Average local ancestry\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Density\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"Average={avg_lanc.mean() * 100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e12c4d66-6a55-4aad-a49f-007e5d288605",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Global ancestry\n",
    "We first merge the simulated dataset with 1,000 Genomes reference data.\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# joint PCA with 1kg\n",
    "ref_pfile=example_data/1kg-ref    # path to 1kg pgen file (all chromosomes)\n",
    "out_dir=example_data/joint-pca    # path to output directory\n",
    "\n",
    "mkdir -p ${out_dir}\n",
    "\n",
    "plink2 --pfile ${ref_pfile} \\\n",
    "       --freq counts \\\n",
    "       --pca allele-wts \\\n",
    "       --out ${out_dir}/ref_pcs\n",
    "\n",
    "for name in 1kg-ref CEU-YRI; do\n",
    "    plink2 --pfile example_data/${name} \\\n",
    "       --read-freq ${out_dir}/ref_pcs.acount \\\n",
    "       --score ${out_dir}/ref_pcs.eigenvec.allele 2 5 header-read no-mean-imputation \\\n",
    "               variance-standardize \\\n",
    "       --score-col-nums 6-15 \\\n",
    "       --out ${out_dir}/${name}\n",
    "done\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Then we plot the PCA with 1,000 Genomes reference and the simulated dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "11d18dc1-bf3c-4996-b689-ead3839d309b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, '1kg reference + simulated')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1125x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pca_dir = \"example_data/joint-pca\"\n",
    "\n",
    "pca_df = pd.read_csv(f\"{pca_dir}/1kg-ref.sscore\", sep='\\t', index_col=0).rename(columns = {f\"PC{i}_AVG\": f\"PC{i}\" for i in range(1, 11)})\n",
    "sample_df = pd.read_csv(f\"{pca_dir}/CEU-YRI.sscore\", sep='\\t', index_col=0).rename(columns = {f\"PC{i}_AVG\": f\"PC{i}\" for i in range(1, 11)})\n",
    "\n",
    "sample_df['SuperPop'] = \"SAMPLE\"\n",
    "pca_df = pd.concat([pca_df, sample_df], axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 4), dpi=125, ncols=2, sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "admix.plot.joint_pca(\n",
    "    df_pc=pca_df,\n",
    "    axes=axes,\n",
    "    x=\"PC1\",\n",
    "    y=\"PC2\",\n",
    "    sample_alpha=0.15,\n",
    "    label_col=\"SuperPop\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "axes[0].set_title(\"1kg reference\")\n",
    "axes[1].set_title(\"1kg reference + simulated\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "5fa23280-7604-423d-a7cf-d8105fb86682",

   "source": [
    "geno, snp_df, indiv_df = dapgen.read_plink(\"example_data/1kg-ref.pgen\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# sanity check for the consistency of frequency calculated in the reference data sets\n",
    "# and the frequency calculated in the admixed data set\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 2.5), dpi=150, ncols=2)\n",
    "for i, anc in enumerate([\"CEU\", \"YRI\"]):\n",
    "    axes[i].scatter(\n",
    "        geno[:, indiv_df.Population == anc].mean(axis=1) / 2, dset.af_per_anc()[:, i], s=0.5\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    axes[i].set_title(anc)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_xlabel(\"Frequency in reference\")\n",
    "    axes[i].set_ylabel(\"Frequency in admixed\")\n",
    "    axes[i].plot([0, 1], [0, 1], \"k--\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()"
   ]
  }
